                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Roberts, K. L. & Smith, G. L.</span>: <span class="ti">Vaccinia virus morphogenesis and dissemination.</span> <span class='so'>Trends Microbiol., 16, 472-479 (2008)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18789694" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>Valderrama, F., Cordeiro, J. V., Schleich, S. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Vaccinia virus-induced cell motility requires F11L-mediated inhibition of RhoA signaling.</span> <span class='so'>Science, 311, 377-381 (2006)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16424340" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Arakawa, Y., Cordeiro, J. V. & Way, M.</span>: <span class="ti">F11L-mediated inhibition of RhoA-mDia signaling stimulates microtubule dynamics during vaccinia virus infection.</span> <span class='so'>Cell Host Microbe, 1, 213-226 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18005700" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Arakawa, Y., Cordeiro, J. V., Schleich, S. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">The release of vaccinia virus from infected cells requires RhoA-mDia modulation of cortical actin.</span> <span class='so'>Cell Host Microbe, 1, 227-240 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18005701" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Cordeiro, J. V., Guerra, S., Arakawa, Y. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">F11-mediated inhibition of RhoA signalling enhances the spread of vaccinia virus in vitro and in vivo in an intranasal mouse model of infection.</span> <span class='so'>PLoS One, 4, e8506 (2009)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20041165" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Ridley, A. J.</span>: <span class="ti">Rho proteins: linking signaling with membrane trafficking.</span> <span class='so'>Traffic, 2, 303-310 (2001)[<a